lg.l:
It appears from these 2 Lines in ye Poem of Cadenus & Vanessa that she had a considerable Fortune──
Five thousand Guineas in her Purse
The Doctor might have fancyd worse.
And yet he refused ye generous offers she made of her Love, tho she was young beautiful & rich.
And calld for his Poetick works.
Mean time ye Boy in secret lurks.
And while ye Book was in her Hand
The Urchin, from his private Stand,
Took Aim: & shot with all his strength
A Dart of such prodigious length,
It pierc'd ye feeble Volume through;
And deep transfixd her Bosom too.
Some Lines, more moving than ye rest
Stuck to ye Point that piercd her Breast,
And born directly to the Heart,
With Pains unknown increas'd her Smart.
Vanessa, not in Years a score,
Dreams of a Gown of fourty four:
In Eyes with Reading, almost blind.
Declin'd in Health, advanc'd in Years.
She fancy's Musick in his Tongue;
Nor further looks, but thinks him young.
In every Scene had kept his heart;
For pastime, or to shew his Wit.
He now could praise, esteem, approve
But understood not what was Love.
His conduct might have made him styl'd
A Father, and ye Nymph his Child.
To see the virgin mind her Book,
Was but the Master's secret Joy
In School to hear ye finest Boy.
She hourly press'd for something new &c
